{
  "number": 1305,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1305",
  "title": "Cannot share custom component within Menu.connect and RefinementList.connect",
  "body": "We cannot share custom components within Menu.connect and RefinementList.connect. This was a feedback from @GregoryPotdevin here: https://gitter.im/algolia/instantsearch.js?at=57da5121df21a75730fbd208\n\nMenu connectors:\n- selectedItem\n- items\n- refine, expects single value\n- createURL expects single value\n\nRefinementList connector:\n- selectedItems\n- items\n- refine, expects array of values\n- createURL expects array of values\n\nEvery connector rendering a list of items should provide the exact same API for consistency and ease of use.\n\nSomething like:\n- items[{value, isRefined, name, toggleState}]\n- refine(item.toggleState)\n- createURL(item.toggleState)\n- defaultRefinement\n\nLinked to #1304, what do you think?\n",
  "created_at": "2016-09-19T20:33:24Z",
